;provides the Schmidt quasi-normalized Legendre functions;   N:       Degree of the Schmidt quasi-normalized Legendre function;   M:       Order of the Schmidt quasi-normalized Legendre function;   N and M can be arbritary as long as M le N, 0 ge M ge N, N ge 1;   ;INRAD=1 if InTheta is given in radians.;   InTheta: The angle (in degrees, unless specified by INRAD keyword);;written by Peter Kollmann, inspired byDrake A. Ranquist's getLegendre procedurefunction getLegendre2, n, m, inTheta, INRAD=inRadIF NOT KEYWORD_SET(inRad) THEN inRad=0theta = inThetaIF NOT inRad THEN theta = inTheta*!Pi/180;;note that (-1)^m  factor is in Mathlab documentation and the comments in getLegendre by Drake but not in Winch 2005. Factor seems to be needed though.IF m ne 0 THEN Pnm=(-1)^m *sqrt(factorial(n-m)*2d/factorial(n+m))*legendre(cos(inTheta),n,m,/double) ELSE Pnm=legendre(cos(inTheta),n,m,/double)return,PnmEND